}
}
return 0;
}
```
this code defines a vector of strings and the regular expression pattern. it then loops through each string in the vector and checks if it matches the pattern using `std::regex_match()`. if the string matches the pattern, it prints the string to the console. running this code will output:
```
hello world abc
```
this is the only string in the provided list that matches the pattern.

you can modify the c++ code to extract only the "hello" substring from the matched strings using capture groups in the regular expression pattern and `std::smatch` in the code. here's the modified code:

