8. use entity framework to retrieve the saved activities from the database and display them in the datagridview. use the following code to retrieve and display the activities:
```
private void selfcaretrackerform_load(object sender, eventargs e)
{
using (var context = new selfcaretrackercontext())
{
dgvactivities.datasource = context.activities.tolist();
}
}
```
9. add validation to the form to ensure that required fields are filled out before saving the data. use the following code to add validation:
```
private void btnsave_click(object sender, eventargs e)
{
if (string.isnullorwhitespace(txtname.text) || string.isnullorwhitespace(txtdescription.text))
{
messagebox.show("please enter a name and description for the activity.");
return;
}
using (var context = new selfcaretrackercontext())
{
var activity = new activity
{
name = txtname.text,
date = dtpdate.value,
description = txtdescription.text
};
context.activities.add(activity);
context.savechanges();
}
dgvactivities.datasource = null;
using (var context = new selfcaretrackercontext())
{
dgvactivities.datasource = context.activities.tolist();
}
txtname.text = "";
txtdescription.text = "";
}
```
10. add five example self-care activities to the form for users to track. use the following code to add the examples:
